feedback.body:
@openhands Investigate and understand this error. Then, if it fails because of the LLM class validation, then clone yourself agent-sdk and investigate that too. LLM should be able to be created without an api key, though maybe it should be non-None, but empty needs to be fine then. Make an issue in that case, in agent-sdk repo, then fix it if it was what is really happening, but it’s okay if you decide it’s not.

Similarly, if the error is from ConversationInfo, it should accept either None, or empty. Check how it does accept values for llm attribute, and compare with critic, it should still be an LLM class object underneath.

Explain to me in detail WDYT after this investigation. Note that I said LLM should accept some lack of key, if maybe empty, for the reason that the user could set a local LLM which doesn’t need a key, or could set Bedrock with non-key authentication, in which case we would even fail (error from Bedrock) if the user sets a string.
